Carl Whithaus teaches writing at UC Davis.  He has Noteworthy Published Authors written two books (Teaching and Evaluating Writing in the Age of Computers and HighStakes Testing and Writing Across Distances and Disciplines).  When not writing about the impact of IT on literacy practices, Carl can be found watching his kids play soccer, taking them to cello or piano lessons, or digging in the garden.

A video of a talk he gave on Peer Response in SmartSite Forums and Word Docs is available at http://fmfp.ucdavis.edu/winter_08_speakers.php
